\begin_layout Standard
We follow a a proportionality assumption so that the total movements within
 the state coincide with ACS (just the total across sectors but not sector
 by sector).
 In this case, we will be prioritizing the CPS when it comes to intra-state
 movements.
 This is, let's fix a given state 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 and define: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
L^{nj,nk}=\sum_{q}L_{ACS}^{n?,nq}\times\frac{L_{CPS}^{nj,nk}}{\sum_{q}\sum_{h}L_{CPS}^{nh,nq}}\forall n\in US,\:\forall j,k
\]

\end_inset

Note that 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{k}\sum_{j}L^{nj,nk}=\sum_{q}L_{ACS}^{n?,nq}$
\end_inset

 (so the total coincides at the movements within the state regardless of
 the sector but not necessarily sector-by-sector).
 Also note that 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{L^{nj,nk}}{L^{nj,nq}}=\frac{L_{CPS}^{nj,nk}}{L_{CPS}^{nj,nq}}$
\end_inset

 by construction.
\end_layout

